---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Accessibility | Scott's Hospitality">
  <section class="bg-ink pt-32 pb-12 sm:pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-gold-light uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-xs mb-4">Accessibility</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-6xl text-cream mb-5 leading-tight">
        A site built for everyone.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-cream/75 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Our commitment to accessible web design across every Scott's concept —
        and how to reach us if something isn't working for you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-cream-soft py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 space-y-10 text-ink/85 leading-relaxed text-base">

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-ink mb-4">Our commitment</h2>
        <p>
          Scott's Hospitality is committed to making every site in our family
          usable for everyone, including guests who use assistive technology
          such as screen readers, keyboard-only navigation, or browser zoom.
          We treat accessibility as part of how the sites are built — not as
          an afterthought.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-ink mb-4">The standard we follow</h2>
        <p>
          The Scott's Hospitality family of sites is designed and maintained to
          meet the
          <strong class="text-ink">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA</strong>
          — the technical standard most commonly referenced for accessible web
          design in the United States.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Our sites were most recently audited against WCAG 2.1 AA on
          <strong class="text-ink">June 24, 2026</strong>, using the
          <a href="https://github.com/dequelabs/axe-core" class="text-gold-deep underline hover:text-ink">axe-core</a>
          accessibility scanning engine — the same engine used by professional
          accessibility consultancies. We re-run that audit whenever significant
          content or design changes are made.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-ink mb-4">What this covers</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-none">
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start"><span class="text-gold-deep font-bold leading-none">·</span><span>Color and contrast designed to be readable for low-vision users</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start"><span class="text-gold-deep font-bold leading-none">·</span><span>Semantic page structure for screen-reader navigation</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start"><span class="text-gold-deep font-bold leading-none">·</span><span>Keyboard-only access to every interactive element</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start"><span class="text-gold-deep font-bold leading-none">·</span><span>Descriptive alt text on photos and images</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start"><span class="text-gold-deep font-bold leading-none">·</span><span>Form fields with associated labels</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start"><span class="text-gold-deep font-bold leading-none">·</span><span>Page titles and landmarks for assistive-technology orientation</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-ink mb-4">Have a problem? Tell us.</h2>
        <p>
          Accessibility is a moving target — every time we add new content there's
          a chance we missed something. If you encounter a barrier on any of our
          sites, please let us know so we can fix it.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Email
          <a href="mailto:info@scottshospitality.com" class="text-gold-deep underline hover:text-ink font-semibold">info@scottshospitality.com</a>
          and a member of our team will follow up.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-paper border-l-4 border-gold p-6 text-sm text-ink/75">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-ink">Scope note.</strong> This statement covers
          the Scott's Hospitality umbrella site, Scott's Seafood San Jose,
          Scott's Ballroom, and Scott's Provisions. Scott's Social Club is
          operated by a third-party platform partner; their site follows that
          vendor's own accessibility standards. Some embedded services
          (OpenTable, Toast, Google Maps) are hosted by their respective
          vendors and follow those vendors' standards.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
